					Latest Key Developments (Source: Significant Developments)




Addnode Q2 EBITA down at SEK 32.8 million
Friday, 21 Jul 2017 05:00am EDT 
July 21 (Reuters) - ADDNODE GROUP AB (PRUBL) :Q2 NET SALES INCREASED TO SEK 587.5 M (528.4), REPRESENTING GROWTH OF 11 PER CENT.Q2 EBITA SEK 32.8 MILLION VERSUS SEK 37.0 MILLION YEAR AGO. 
			
Full Article





Addnode buys remaining 63 pct in partly owned company behind Kompanion
Thursday, 15 Dec 2016 02:30am EST 
Addnode Group AB (publ) : Says strengthens its offer in e-health and welfare through acquisition of Kompanion . Acquires remaining shares in partly owned company behind Kompanion and will thereby strengthen its offer in e-health and welfare . Acquisition of remaining 63 percent of shares in company will occur on Jan. 2, 2017 .Acquisition is expected to have marginally positive impact on its earnings per share. 
			
Full Article





Addnode gets order from authority within defense and security sector
Friday, 30 Sep 2016 02:30am EDT 
Addnode Group AB : Says its unit, Ida Infront, has signed agreement with authority within defense and security sector . Agreement has order value of about $0.5 million .Agreement includes implementation and support during five years with extension possibility of two more years. 
			
Full Article





Addnode unit gets order to deliver e-archive product to Riksantikvarieämbetet
Monday, 26 Sep 2016 03:21am EDT 
Addnode Group AB (publ) : Unit Ida Infront has via Pulsen AB received order to deliver e-archive product to Riksantikvarieämbetet (Swedish National Heritage Board) .3-year agreement has value of about 1.5 million Swedish crowns ($175,637.86). 
			
Full Article





Addnode Group acquires software supplier Stamford
Monday, 22 Aug 2016 02:30am EDT 
Addnode : Acquires Swedish software supplier Stamford and strengthens its position in the retail and real estate industry . Stamford companies will be merged with Addnode Group's existing subsidiary, Prosilia . Two merged operations will be conducted under name Stamford . Completion takes place on September 1, 2016 .Company will be a part of Addnode Group's business area process management. 
			
Full Article





Addnode Q2 EBITA up at SEK 37.0 million
Friday, 22 Jul 2016 05:00am EDT 
Addnode : Q2 net sales 528.4 million Swedish crowns ($61.50 million) versus 387.3 million crowns year ago . Q2 EBITA 37.0 million crowns versus 22.6 million crowns year ago . Sees major business potential in digitalisation in e-health sector .The board has not changed its assessment of the future outlook compared with the previous quarter. 
			
Full Article





Addnode sets new unit focusing on e-health and pharmacy solutions
Thursday, 7 Jul 2016 02:00am EDT 
Addnode Group AB : Establishes new software company focusing on e-health and pharmacy solutions . Has established a new subsidiary on Norwegian market named Pharmasolutions AS .Company has initiated a partnership with Canella AB and consulting company EY Norway. 
			
Full Article





Addnode Group acquires software company EssVision
Friday, 1 Jul 2016 02:00am EDT 
Addnode Group AB : Acquires software company EssVision AB which had net sales of 13 million Swedish crowns ($1.53 million) during 2015 and operating margin of 17 percent .Completion took place July 1, 2016 and EssVision will be a part of Addnode Group's business area Process Management. 
			
Full Article





Addnode Group AB signs PLM services agreement worth over $2.5 mln
Monday, 2 May 2016 02:00am EDT 
Addnode Group AB:Signs PLM services agreement with a global technology provider.Agreement has an order value of more than $2.5 million over a 12-month period. 
			
Full Article





Addnode Group signs agreement with Inera
Monday, 18 Apr 2016 02:00am EDT 
Addnode Group AB:Addnode Group signs agreement with Inera.Decerno, a subsidiary to Addnode Group, has signed a framework agreement with Inera regarding e-health application management.Agreement spans over a period of four years and holds a potential contract volume of about 80 million - 120 million Swedish crowns ($9.82 million - $14.73 million) annually.A second round of competition will take place among the twelve companies that have signed the framework agreement with Inera. 
			
Full Article





